latestPosts.caption:
“Strength isn’t built overnight. It’s forged swing by swing.”

The Mudgar is a traditional Indian wooden mace used for centuries by warriors, wrestlers (pehelwans), and yogis to build functional strength, endurance, grip, and focus. Rooted in ancient akhada (wrestling gym) culture, the Mudgar isn’t just a tool—it’s a discipline.

Crafted from solid wood and swung in circular patterns, it enhances mobility, develops core strength, and trains the body in dynamic, rotational movement—something modern fitness often misses.

Often associated with Lord Hanuman, the deity of strength and devotion, the Mudgar embodies both physical power and spiritual dedication.
